.TH SHARE 1 "2026-05-04" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
share \- enable or disable a Samba share availability
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B share
.B {enable|disable}
.B sharename
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B share
is a shell script designed to automate the process of toggling the availability of a 
specific Samba share within the /etc/samba/smb.conf configuration file. 
.PP
The script modifies the \fBavailable\fR parameter within the specified share section, 
setting it to \fByes\fR for the \fBenable\fR action or \fBno\fR for the \fBdisable\fR 
action.
.PP
This script must be executed with superuser privileges (e.g., via \fBsudo\fR).
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B enable
Sets the \fBavailable\fR parameter for the specified share to \fByes\fR.
.TP
.B disable
Sets the \fBavailable\fR parameter for the specified share to \fBno\fR.
.TP
.B sharename
The name of the share section to be modified as defined in /etc/samba/smb.conf.
.SH BEHAVIOR
.IP "Configuration Management:"
The script performs an in-place edit of /etc/samba/smb.conf. Before applying any 
changes, the script creates a backup of the original configuration file with a 
\text{.bak} extension.
.IP "Validation:"
The script verifies that the requested share exists within the configuration file. 
After modification, it runs \fBtestparm\fR to ensure the new configuration is 
syntactically valid. If the configuration check fails, the script automatically 
reverts the changes using the backup file.
.IP "Process Handling:"
If the script detects that files within the share's defined path are actively being 
accessed by other processes (via \fblsof\fR), it will display a warning. The user 
will be prompted to confirm whether to force-disconnect these processes using 
\fbfuser\fR.
.IP "Service Reload:"
Upon a successful configuration update and validation, the script triggers a reload 
of the Samba configuration using \fbsmbcontrol\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.DT 0
Success.
.DT 1
An error occurred (e.g., insufficient privileges, invalid arguments, share not found, 
or configuration validation failure).
.SH FILES
.DT /etc/samba/smb.conf
The primary Samba configuration file targeted by the script.
.DT /etc/samba/smb.conf.bak
The backup of the configuration file created by the script prior to modification.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR smb.conf (5),
.BR testparm (1),
.BR smbcontrol (1)
